#INT            -   -2147483648 to 2147483647 OR 0 to 4294967295
#FLOAT(M,D)     -   display lengt (M) and number of decimal (D)
#DATE           -   format YYYY-MM-DD, between 1000-01-01 and 9999-12-31. May 17th, 2007 would be stored as 2007-05-17
#DATETIME       -   a date and time combination - format YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS between 1000-01-01 00:00:00 and 9999:12:31 23:59:59.for example,2:20 in the afternoon on July 8th, 2014 would be stored as 2014-07-08 14:20:00
#CHAR(M)        -   a fized-lenght string between 1 and 255 characters
#VARCHAR(M)     -   a variable-lenght string between 1 and 255 characters in lenght. You must define a leng the creating a VARCHAR field
#BLOB or TEXT   -   a field with a maximum lenght of 65535 characters.BLOBs are "Binary Large Objects" and are used to store large amounts of binary data, such as image or other types of files.
